# Studio Profile Template

This directory contains the schema for creating studio profiles.

## Required Files

Each studio should have:
- `profile.json` — Studio metadata (name, location, type, zones)
- `clays.json` — Clay bodies used at the studio
- `glazes/` — Glaze collections (YAML files per collection)

## profile.json Schema

```json
{
  "name": "Studio Name",
  "location": "Address",
  "type": "membership_studio | community_studio | school | production",
  "instagram": "@handle",
  "website": "url",
  "zones": {
    "zone_name": {
      "cone": "5",
      "atmosphere": "oxidation | reduction",
      "clay": "Clay Body Name",
      "kiln_type": "electric | gas | wood"
    }
  }
}
```

## clays.json Schema

```json
{
  "version": "1.0",
  "studio": "Studio Name",
  "last_updated": "YYYY-MM-DD",
  "clays": [
    {
      "name": "Clay Name",
      "cone": "5",
      "type": "stoneware | earthenware | porcelain",
      "firing": "oxidation | reduction",
      "use": "zone_name",
      "notes": "Optional notes"
    }
  ]
}
```

## Glaze Collection YAML Schema

Follow the same format as `default/glazes/member-cone5-oxidation.yaml`.
